BANDARI College is reviewing its curriculum to match with the market needs and demand, the institute Principal, Dr Joseph Kakeneno has announced in Dodoma. The Principal revealed the plan on Tuesday at the ongoing National Council for Technical Training at the Jamhuri Stadium. He said the college decided to review the curriculum after conducting research to see if the current one meets the increasingly technological advancements and market needs. "Before they are in use we will handle them to NACTE for approval and accreditation,’’ said Dr Kakeneno. He outlined the curriculum which have been reviewed are in the fields of freight clearing and forwarding, shipping logistics and ports management, logistics and transport management among others. The Principal said the curriculum review are also meant to address the increasingly changes in market but also attain the industrial drive economy.